# gwiki 0.1 - Simple git based wiki script.

## REQUIREMENTS

- git
- optional: w3m for viewer, otherwise use cat; md2html.awk (https://bitbucket.org/yiyus/md2html.awk)

## SETUP

1. set WIKI_PATH environment variable to path where your wiki files will be 
   stored
2. if you want to write custom commit messages set WIKI_AUTO_COMMIT_MESSAGE
   environment variable to false
3. if you want automaticaly push your changes to remote repository set it
   first (go to your `WIKI_PATH` directory and run command:
   `git remote add origin adress_to_your_repo`) and set WIKI_AUTO_PUSH
   environment variable to true
4. run `gwiki create`

## USAGE

- to add new page run: `gwiki add CATEGORY/SUBCATEGORY/ARTICLE_NAME` where
  ARTICLE_NAME - required, name of article (not it title)
  CATEGORY and SUBCATEGORY are optional and self-explained
- to edit page run: `gwiki edit CATEGORY/SUBCATEGORY/ARTICLE_NAME`
- to delete page run: `gwiki delete CATEGORY/SUBCATEGORY/ARTICLE_NAME`
- to view page run: `gwiki view CATEGORY/SUBCATEGORY/ARTICLE_NAME`
- to list new page run: `gwiki list CATEGORY/SUBCATEGORY/ARTICLE_NAME`

